{"id": "1518676442148241590", "channel_id": "1514217261358121011", "author_id": "250664395749720065", "author_name": "_pdt", "content": "If there is one thing I agree with the rework idea is that the card should lose the \"sabotage\" property after being played.\n\nBut aside from that, the game has many punishing mechanics like the Parasite that makes you take damage for every card played, monsters that make your cards create Status or give STR, Fervor paired with Arc 2 Arith harmony is quite a challenge to deal with, and the worst offender of them all (at least for me) is the new Elite/Boss that can instantly steal your Aliemus because you released Exalt and the monster changed intention.\n\nWhy is Sabotage so much worse than other game mechanics? Numbers are too high?\n(Can't say that last W3A5 was easy, but I had way more problems with other fights.)", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T17:57:59.452000+00:00", "thread_id": "1514217261358121011"}
